node.text: Our first ever YouTuber awards show where we celebrate those in the YouTube fishing world for what they do best.

node.text: Priorities am I right? 😎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 22, 2021. May be a meme of 1 person and text that says 'Friend: Is catching fish based on luck? Me: Well yes, but actually no'.

node.text: It's all about tracking patterns and knowing how to work your bait! But there's a little luck involved too 😏

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'KARL'S TIPS & TRICKS When throwing a popper it can be easy to mindlessly fish a whole bank with a single retrieve. Resist that, and experiment with different retrieves. Bass are notorious for responding differently to different cadences.'.

node.text: Start out with a quick “pop-pop-pause”, and then insert longer pauses, harder or softer pops, and even extremely slow or fast retrieves!

node.text: The @13fishing JABBER JAW is a crankbait that's had a face transplant—and the donor was a bladed jig! It's got an erratic wobble and rolling action while adding the frantic vibration of a chatterbait! Find it in my shop 🔥🔥🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 DOCK TIPS'.

node.text: What tips do you have for fishing docks?⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 DOCK TIPS'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says '1.BE QUIET You don't wanna spook fish that are holding tight to the dock, so keep your approach quiet Try lightly flipping and pitching your bait near it, or cast past your spot and work the bait back through it.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. WALKWAYS It's easy to only want to fish the end of the dock where the deepest water is, but don't forget about the walkways and Shoee Especially during spawn or if water levels are high, there are sure to be fish pushed up shallow. So always remember to fish the whole dock!'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. CURRENTS If you're fishing a dock on a current, try to stay as close to the pilings as possible. Game fish will often sit right between the pilings to catch a break from the current, and ambush baitfish getting pushed along.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4. BE NICE If you do happen to snag your bait on rope, or get it tangled around the post, be sure to retrieve it. This keeps swimmers safe and is the respectful thing to do! Also, be careful of other people's boats and property, especially if you have a heavy jig tied on.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FISHING RIDDLE Four men were fishing in a boat on the lake. The boat turned over and all four men fell in the lake. And yet, not one single man got wet. How can this be?'.

node.text: COMMENT what you think the answer is 🧠🧠🧠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 WAYS TO BE A BETTER NET MAN 1. Have the net ready to go nearby, not tangled up in some fishing line. 2. Give your buddy enough room to fight the fish. Stay off to the side. 3. Don't rush the landing. Let the rod do most of the work, try not to chase the fish with the net. 4. Don't lunge forward and stab the fish, instead, use a scooping motion.'.
